g.text: EleanorRank4Convo7 begins.

g.title: j681453232
g.text: I wanted to ask you something, but I’m not sure how you’ll take it, so if I’m out of order please say so.

g.title: j3770221851
g.text: Okay.

g.title: j1370476734
g.text: What were your parents like?

g.title: j3094066784
g.text: It’s been so long I can barely remember.

g.title: j386870662
g.text: Kind. They tried to do right by me.

g.title: j989501613
g.text: Strict. They were in charge and they let me know it.

g.title: j1229286842
g.text: Hopeless. I might as well have been raised by feral Kubrows.

g.title: j2421651062
g.text: I... can't do this. Sorry. [End.]

g.title: j1942295712
g.text: I'm sorry. I stupidly assumed that because your memories of the Zariman were so vivid, you'd be able to recall your parents, too.

g.title: j1012736195
g.text: I'm glad. If you don't mind me saying so, it shows.

g.title: j3165854917
g.text: I didn't think you'd had a soft upbringing. I suppose colonists need to be tough.

g.title: j3366768967
g.text: Oh dear. Well, for what it's worth, you made a bloody decent human being of yourself.

g.title: j1931820228
g.text: No, I'm sorry. I had no right to ask.

g.title: j2893786572
g.text: I forget how many lifetimes you've lived.

g.title: j300549522
g.text: There's a warm flame of kindness in you, and I was wondering who had helped to kindle it.

g.title: j3140615145
g.text: With those Orokin in charge, it's a wonder anyone turned out decent.

g.title: j1560963243
g.text: I only wish you could have had an easier time of it.

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j2962949771
g.text: Boolean DrifterParentsUnknown is now true.

g.title: j1766699482
g.text: Boolean DrifterParentsKind is now true.

g.title: j1011860944
g.text: Boolean DrifterParentsStrict is now true.

g.title: j1763516039
g.text: Boolean DrifterParentsUseless is now true.

g.title: j1611360385
g.text: Why do you ask?

g.title: j1310029682
g.text: I was thinking about mine. I do it a lot, actually. I sit on my arse and wonder what Mum and Dad would think about how their kids ended up.

g.title: j2176355304
g.text: What were they like as people?

g.title: j2726871824
g.text: What were they like as parents?

g.title: j2247777626
g.text: As people they were radically mismatched, which means they had the kind of relationship that burns hot and bright for the first few years and then collapses into a sucking black hole after that.

g.title: j1502404797
g.text: Incompatible, in a word. Dad wanted us to be independent, so he'd engineer situations where we had to be. Dropping us off in the woods with just a penknife, that sort of thing. Mum was always coming to the rescue. It was doomed.

g.title: j2832264540
g.text: Dad is ex-army. Jovial, little wrinkly eyes, speaks like a newsreader, so broken on the inside that if you picked him up and shook him he’d rattle like a bag of gravel. He’s surprisingly easy to upset. I’ve tossed off comments that I thought were mild, then overheard him crying in the loo later on.

g.title: j2745059368
g.text: Arthur and I quickly learned to play them off against one another. You know how kids are.

g.title: j1394355693
g.text: Mum’s lot were richer, which meant she had a long leash. She didn’t go down the party path, wine and drugs and weeklong binges in Ludston flats. That was more Aunt Janice’s gig. Mum is more flowers, pottery hedgehogs, pot-pourri and everything being Nice.

g.title: j2343758667
g.text: Parents always overcompensate for whatever they feel their own parents did wrong, don't they?

g.title: j1322537222
g.text: Half of what you’re saying might as well be Voidtongue, but I think I get it.

g.title: j119251453
g.text: Well, they’re divorced now. They waited until we were out of our teens to do it, out of ‘consideration’. That was kind, don’t you think? Forcing us to live in a bloody battleground of a house because Kids Need Stability or some such garbage.

g.title: j948440732
g.text: Are you still in touch?

g.title: j4185327279
g.text: Once in a while. We used to go back home for Solstice. Now that I do miss. Decorating the star-tree, crowning Sol, little kids going door to door dressed as Lua’s Three Aspects, roasting the bird… it’s sentimental, but I genuinely love it.

g.title: j905105842
g.text: Mum and Dad always had a peace treaty for Solstice and they always respected it. On a good year they managed to keep from ripping into each other until after Third Day, even with the plum brandy flowing.

g.title: j2461600862
g.text: If you just felt a massive wave of homesickness wash over you, that was me. Sorry.

g.title: j1952455220
g.text: I try to keep the big emotions to myself but sometimes they just boil over like milk in a pot, and everyone cops it. Then it’s on to the old KIM for a round of apologies.

g.title: j2025858050
g.text: Why bring them up now?

g.title: j3904828210
g.text: I was just wondering what they’d make of you. If we ever get out of this place, I’d like to rock up to Solstice dinner with my time-traveling friend.

g.title: j2485761936
g.text: I think you’d like it. You and Dad and Arthur could sit by the fire and trade war stories, and Mum could gently prod you about whether you were single.

g.title: j2347314570
g.text: I think I’d horrify them.

g.title: j1584193799
g.text: I'd be on my best behavior, for your sake.

g.title: j1540509329
g.text: Honestly, that sounds like fun.

g.title: j1794603687
g.text: Single? Wait, would I be coming home as a partner?

g.title: j666781044
g.text: +15 Chemistry

g.title: j3875226766
g.text: +15 Chemistry

g.title: j3766028591
g.text: +15 Chemistry

g.title: j2900829949
g.text: Um.

g.title: j3833563174
g.text: HA! That just makes me want to do it more.

g.title: j2228857417
g.text: That's so sweet of you!

g.title: j497101250
g.text: Oh Gods, let's do it. If we ever get the chance, we'll make it real.

g.title: j1919111432
g.text: This took a turn, she said, fanning herself.

g.title: j1416939060
g.text: I can just see Dad politely asking "so was it always death by impalement, or did they try to vary it up a bit?"

g.title: j3352900137
g.text: ... I should let go of this dream before I try to make it happen. We are here, this is now, and there's still a war on.

g.title: j2901113648
g.text: Thank you.

g.title: j3124675904
g.text: Would you WANT to?

g.title: j2740489413
g.text: I'm going to dream about this. Thank you.

g.title: j3815100772
g.text: Thank you for a beautiful dream.

g.title: j273930549
g.text: I've got one more thing to get out of bed in the morning for, now.

g.title: j2023376858
g.text: Honestly? Yes.

g.title: j2619208751
g.text: No. I just wasn’t sure what you were imagining.

g.title: j2855717238
g.text: Uh… can I get back to you on that?

g.title: j2488951032
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j603994615
g.text: Right.

g.title: j3794555383
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j3469803946
g.text: You are an absolutely exasperating person.

g.title: j2187318911
g.text: Sorry.

g.title: j3660581972
g.text: Yes.

g.title: j1749779535
g.text: I’m trying to have a perfectly innocent conversation about parents, with no ulterior motive, and now you’ve gone and knocked me sideways.

g.title: j2755470725
g.text: My mistake.

g.title: j796238718
g.text: By all means.

g.title: j2598951815
g.text: Boolean EleanorConfession is now true.

g.title: j1984766901
g.text: We have time, and none of us is going anywhere, are we?

g.title: j1204195978
g.text: I'm going to have to give this the serious consideration it deserves. FFS.
